<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I work the northern corridor regularly and understand how Aspley sits in the buyer decision. The suburb draws a specific profile: families who have done their research on Aspley State High School and identified the catchment as a genuine priority, northside upgraders who want more block than inner-north suburbs can deliver at the same budget, and buyers who work in the northern corridor and want a practical commute. What they find in Aspley is a suburb with real land content, retail convenience at the Aspley Homemaker Centre and Westfield Chermside nearby, and a community character shaped by decades of stable owner-occupation.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Gympie Road provides the primary arterial connection south toward the CBD, with bus services running along both Gympie Road and the Carseldine corridor. Off-peak the drive to the CBD takes approximately 20 to 25 minutes. The housing mix runs from original post-war homes through to a growing number of renovated and rebuilt properties, with the strongest demand consistently sitting on internal streets where block sizes are more generous and the streetscape is well established. The Aspley Homemaker Centre precinct anchors the suburb's identity as a retail destination for the broader northern suburbs, adding everyday convenience that buyers weigh alongside school catchment when they make their decision.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Aspley Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Northern Brisbane Corridor</p>
