        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Aspley property values are driven by the Aspley State High School catchment, block size, and proximity to the Aspley Homemaker Centre and Westfield Chermside. Homes on generous blocks in quiet internal streets away from Gympie Road consistently attract family buyers comparing the suburb favourably against Wavell Heights and Kedron at a more accessible price point.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Aspley?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Aspley homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days. The suburb draws buyers from across the northern corridor, particularly families prioritising the Aspley State High School catchment and buyers who want more land than comparable price points in Wavell Heights or Kedron can offer. Practical access to Gympie Road and strong everyday retail amenity helps sustain a broad buyer pool.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Aspley?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Aspley offers a relaxed, family-oriented lifestyle approximately 12 kilometres north of the CBD. Strong everyday retail at the Aspley Homemaker Centre and Westfield Chermside nearby, bus connectivity along Gympie Road, and quiet internal streets with generous blocks make it a practical and comfortable place to raise a family. The suburb's high proportion of long-term owner-occupiers contributes to a stable, well-maintained neighbourhood character.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Aspley a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Aspley offers a compelling combination of land size, school catchment quality and retail amenity at a price point that compares well with more established northern suburbs closer to the CBD. Buyers who find Wavell Heights or Kedron beyond their budget consistently discover that Aspley offers comparable fundamentals with more space. As the northern corridor continues to attract buyer attention, Aspley's structural appeal is gaining broader recognition.</p>
